This paper is related to the design of hybrid precoder and combiner in millimeter wave (mmWave) multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which involves signal processing, communication theory, and networking. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which focuses on the fundamental limits of data communication and storage. The second likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing, analysis, and retrieval of multimedia data, including audio, video, and images. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which studies the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems, including communication networks. The fourth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which covers the design, analysis, and optimization of computer networks and protocols. The fifth likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning, which are relevant to the digital signal processing and optimization techniques used in this paper.
